<chapter id="features">
<title>Features</title>

<note><para>
The most important features are listed here, but it would make this list too
long if we were to
display <emphasis>all</emphasis> the features and improvements.
You will discover even more features in this documentation and in the &changelog_url; file.
</para></note>

<para>
<itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
     <para>Configurable &main_toolbar_lnk; and
           <link linkend="key_bindings">key-bindings</link>.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
     <para>Supported &archives_lnk; : ace, arj, bzip2, gzip, iso, lha, rar, rpm, tar and zip.
     </para></listitem>
  <listitem>

      <para><link linkend="krusearcher">Advanced search module</link> that can search in archives.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="compare-dir">Directory comparison</link> and
            <link linkend="view-menu">filtering</link>.</para>
  </listitem>

   <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="panels">(Pre)View and Tree panels</link>.</para>
   </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para>&remote_connections_lnk; &eg; &FTP;/SAMBA with SFTP/SCP support.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para>Open a <link linkend="commands-menu">Terminal</link> &eg;
&konsole;, defaults to the browsed path.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para>Built-in &termemu_lnk;.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para>A &cmdline_lnk; capable of running something in a terminal with a single click
             of a button.</para>
   </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="bookman">Bookmark-Manager</link>.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para>Easy editing of <link linkend="file-menu">file permissions</link>
and ownership.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para>Shows the <link linkend="panels">effective permissions for the current user</link>.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="calculate">Calculates occupied space</link> by marked files and folders.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para>Internal <link linkend="krviewer">viewer and configurable editor.</link></para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para>Completely supports drag'n'drop: drag from &konqueror; straight into a .tar.gz file, from
       &krusader;'s panel into the trash-bin, the desktop or into &konqueror;!</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para><link linkend="unpacking-archives">Packs (or unpacks) files</link> into a single archive
       of your choice without typing a single command.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para><link linkend="test-archive">Tests the integrity of archives</link>.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para><link linkend="compare-files">Compare files by content</link> (via external diff program
        such as &kompare;, &kdiff3_url;  or &xxdiff_url;).</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para>Fully <link linkend="konfig-general">mimetype-aware</link> (with or
without "magic"!).</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para>Built-in Mount-Manager &mountman_lnk;.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="multi_rename">Krename</link> support, a very powerful
                                external batch renamer for &kde;,
seamlessly integrated.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
     <para>&foldertabs_lnk;</para>
  </listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>


